4 HR____ DESIGNATING THE MONTH OF MAY 2026 AS JEWISH AMERICAN
5 HERITAGE MONTH.
6
7 WHEREAS, Jewish citizens have been part of Alabama's
8 history since at least 1785 and have played an important
9 role in the development of this state, contributing
10 significantly to Alabama's culture, history, economy, and
11 civic life; and
12 WHEREAS, Jewish American Heritage Month is an annual
13 celebration of the history, culture, and contributions of
14 Jewish Americans and an opportunity to recognize the
15 enduring legacy of Jewish faith and tradition in the United
16 States; and
17 WHEREAS, the Jewish community has faced historical
18 struggles and challenges, including discrimination and
19 persecution, yet has demonstrated resilience and a deep
20 commitment to justice, compassion, and service; and
21 WHEREAS, the Jewish tenet of tikkun olam, meaning
22 "repairing the world," has inspired generations to pursue
23 justice, charitable service, and civic engagement within
24 Alabama communities; and
25 WHEREAS, Jewish American Heritage Month provides an
26 opportunity to promote understanding, acceptance, and
27 respect among people of all faiths and backgrounds; and
28 WHEREAS, since 2006, the month of May has been
Page 1

WHEREAS, since 2006, the month of May has been
HR264 INTRODUCED
29 proclaimed by the President of the United States as Jewish
30 American Heritage Month pursuant to a bipartisan resolution
31 of Congress; now therefore,
32 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
33 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That the month of May 2026 is hereby
34 designated as Jewish American Heritage Month in Alabama.
35 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That the citizens of Alabama
36 are encouraged to observe this month through education,
37 reflection, and recognition of the lasting contributions of
38 Jewish Americans to this state and nation; and
39 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That a copy of this
40 resolution be transmitted to representatives of Alabama's
41 Jewish community in recognition of this observance.
